<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-20139] Remove `REPEATED_TESTS` env var from repeated tests script</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20139</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Quick follow-on from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18942&quot; title=&quot;Repeatable java test runs on jenkins&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-18942&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-18942&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The use of REPEATED_TESTS doesn&apos;t work with the dockerised scripts (see this &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18942?focusedCommentId=17904409&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-17904409&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;comment&lt;/a&gt;), and duplicates the `-t` functionality.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Easiest solution is to just remove it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
